# Alembic Migrations - Review Hub

## Comandos Úteis

### Gerar nova migration (autogenerate)
```bash
cd backend
source .venv/bin/activate
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "description"
```

### Aplicar migrations
```bash
alembic upgrade head
```

### Reverter última migration
```bash
alembic downgrade -1
```

### Ver histórico
```bash
alembic history
```

### Ver status atual
```bash
alembic current
```

## Notas

- O banco PostgreSQL deve estar rodando (Supabase local ou Docker)
- As migrations usam async com asyncpg
- Os modelos são detectados automaticamente via `app.models`
